Automobile production by U.S.manufacturers this week will be 2.5 pct below output for thesame week last year, according to Automotive News.    The trade paper said 167,942 cars will be made in theUnited States this week, down from 172,348 during last year'sweek.    Production will also be below last week's level, when173,596 cars were made, the paper estimated.    Truck output this week will be 79,784 vehicles, ahead ofthe 76,059 units made during the same week last year but behindthe 80,424 trucks made last week. Reuter&#3;